# elementary-script - Being updated

A tiny script that helps you perform necessary tasks after you install elementary OS or others Ubuntu based systems.

![Screenshot](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/naaando/elementary-script/master/Screenshot.png)

## OS Version Compatibility

elementary-script will always support the lastest stable version of elementary OS, which at the moment is **elementary OS 0.4.1 Loki** and others Ubuntu based systems.

## Run

#### with curl

```shell
bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/naaando/elementary-script/master/elementary-script.sh)"
```

#### with wget

```shell
bash -c "$(wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/naaando/elementary-script/master/elementary-script.sh -O -)"
```
#### Cloning git

Copy and paste the following line into a terminal window in order to run the script.

```bash
sudo apt install git
git clone https://github.com/naaando/elementary-script
cd elementary-script
./elementary-script.sh
```

